net.hudup.core.data

Class Attribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.Attribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class Attribute
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cloneable, TextParsable, java.io.Serializable
    As a convention this class is called attribute. Attribute indicates the data type, which is also a wrapper of data type. Such type is represented by the internal Attribute.Type of this class. In current implementation, there are seven data types as follows:
    • bit: binary, boolean.
    • nominal: discrete and non-number data such as weekdays (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday).
    • integer: integer number.
    • real: real number.
    • string: text data.
    • date: date and time.
    • object: any type.
    Attribute provides many methods for processing data type and retrieving information from data type. Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, uses attribute. Profile has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses attribute to specify its data types but applications of attribute are very large. For convenience, attribute can be considered as field in database table. The concept of attribute is derived from the concept of attribute in Weka - Data Mining Software in Java, available at http://www.cs.waikato.ac.nz/ml/weka
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

    • Field Detail

      • name

        protected java.lang.String name
        Name of attribute.

      • type

        protected Attribute.Type type
        Internal data type of this attribute. Default value of this type is Attribute.Type.object (anything).

      • index

        protected int index
        The index of this attribute. This index is only meaningful if this attribute is a member of attribute list. Note that attribute list is represented by AttributeList. For example, if this attribute is the first element in attribute list, its index is 0. When the index is -1, this attribute is not attached with any attribute list. Default value of this index is -1.

      • isKey

        protected boolean isKey
        If this value is true, this attribute is key attribute used to distinguish two records (two profiles). Exactly, in a profile, a key attribute or a set of some key attributes are used to distinguish two profiles. If there is only one key attribute, we state that the profile has single key. A integer single key is also called identification (ID). If there are a set of key attributes, we state that the profile has complex key. Single key and complex key are represented by the Keys class. Default value of this variable is false.

      • autoInc

        protected boolean autoInc
        If this value is true, this attribute is auto-increment attribute. For example, suppose a record (profile) whose first value is an integer and has auto-increment attribute; when a new record (profile) is inserted, the value of such record is increased automatically. Default value of this variable is false. Note that the auto-increment is only effective if this attribute has integer type; otherwise, the auto-increment is ignored.

      • nominalList

        protected NominalList nominalList
        In case that type of this attribute indicates nominal type called nominal in brief, this variable is the list of nominal (s). Nominal indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday). Nominal is represented by Nominal and nominal list is represented by NominalList. This variable is the empty nominal list.
